channel.title: I suck
channel.description:
Alright so basically all I want is for a real person to double check that I have JDK properly installed on my computer with environment variables correct and everything.
SO here is what I've got.
Installed JDK 6u14 to C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.6.0_14
Path variable: C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.6.0_14\bin;.
Classpath didn't exist in system variables so i created it like this "Classpath" and for the value
Classpath variable: CLASSPATH=C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.6.0_14\bin;%CLASSPATH%;
Seriously thanks for helping.
Also now that I have Java installed, does that mean if I click the start new server button in moparscape and use my internal IP (127.0.0.1) it will work? b/c i'm pretty sure it's a webclient right?
(I'm asking this because i have so far been unsuccessful in playing in any private server in moparscape, including my internal IP address one from the Start Server button)
(and no I'm not stupid nor retarded, I just don't know a lot about Java, and while I'm all for reading, I appreciate the help from a real person more.)
